<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-22T04:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-22T04:41:00-05:00" n="479" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5631/222: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Emmet</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">The
                                            Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-22T11:00:00+01:19">June 22, 1935—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 22—5:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>46. Legation’s No. 45, June 21, 4 p.m. Explanation of the reaction of
                                the Netherlands authorities to our list of desiderata, I have been
                                told this morning, is this: They fear that if they accept our list
                                in its present form as a basis for negotiation they will <hi rend="italic">ipso facto</hi> admit that they are willing to
                                give consideration to the suppression of quotas.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Emmet</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>